The canonical instructions for this repository are in **[AGENTS.md](/AGENTS.md)**
(Cursor also reads `AGENTS.md` natively; this rule guarantees it is always in
context). Read it before editing.

Key rules (full set in `AGENTS.md` and each `packages/*/AGENTS.md`):

- shadcn design system: `@chatool/core` ships standard CSS variables
  (`--background`, `--primary`, `--radius`, etc.) mapped to Tailwind utilities via
  `@theme inline`. Style with token utilities (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`,
  `rounded-md`, `border-border`), never raw hex; apps re-theme by overriding standard variables.
  See `docs/conventions/shadcn.md`.
- tsdown preserves `"use client"` / `"use server"` natively, but only at the top
  of an entry's own source — re-export barrels keep the directive explicitly.
- Keep `exports` maps correct; every package is `"type": "module"` with dual
  ESM/CJS output (`.mjs`/`.d.mts` + `.cjs`/`.d.cts`).
- Server Components by default: pure components ship no directive; add
  `"use client";` only for client features (hooks/context/event-wiring/browser
  APIs/client-only deps). When in doubt add it (the Vite warning is harmless).
  See `docs/conventions/client-server-components.md`.
- `@chatool/ui` components: one kebab-case directory each (`button/` → `index.tsx`
  barrel + `button.tsx` arrow component + `*.types.ts` / `*.variants.ts` + optional
  `useLogic`); arrow, one-per-file, default-exported; client components carry
  `"use client";` on the view file **and** the `index.tsx` entry barrel. Icons
  exempt. ESLint-enforced for `packages/ui/src/**`. See
  `docs/conventions/component-structure.md`.
- Registry-agnostic; every functional change needs a Changeset.

Edit rules in `AGENTS.md`, not here.
